## Limitations
The findings are based on available data and may not encompass all perspectives or the latest research developments. The lack of a universally accepted guideline for screen time means recommendations can vary significantly. Additionally, individual differences among teenagers, such as their maturity level and personal circumstances, can influence the appropriateness of screen time limits.